  - TOKEN_USAGE: Prompt=85648, Gen=379
  - STATE_UPDATE: {'solution_plan': "Now I have the complete solution. Let me summarize:\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe build fails because of a Go 1.25+ compatibility issue with the `go-118-fuzz-build` tool:\n\n1. **Go 1.25+ restriction**: Go 1.25+ strictly forbids overlay replacements for files under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/`).\n\n2. **Toolchain under GOMODCACHE**: When `go.mod` specifies `go 1.25.7`, Go downloads the toolchain to `/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`, which is under `GOMODCACHE`.\n\n3. **Overlay conflict**: The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `$GOROOT/src/testing/fuzz.go` and `$GOROOT/src/testing/testing.go`. Since `GOROOT` points to the toolchain under `GOMODCACHE`, Go 1.25+ rejects the overlay.\n\n## Fix\n\nThe fix adds a workaround in `build.sh` that copies the Go toolchain from its location under `GOMODCACHE` to `/tmp/gotoolchain` (outside `GOMODCACHE`), then sets `GOROOT` to this copy. This way, the overlay replacements target paths outside `GOMODCACHE`, and Go 1.25+ accepts them.\n\n[HYPOTHESIS-DRIVEN]: The fix is derived from analyzing the Go 1.25+ overlay restriction and the `go-118-fuzz-build` tool's overlay generation logic. The solution copies the toolchain outside GOMODCACHE to bypass the restriction."}
